usage: zeek-client [-h] [--controller HOST:PORT] [--verbose]
                   {monitor,instances,set-config} ...

A zeek-client prototype

optional arguments:
  -h, --help            show this help message and exit
  --controller HOST:PORT
                        Address and port of the controller, either of which
                        may be omitted (default: 127.0.0.1:2150)
  --verbose, -v         Increase program output for debugging. Use multiple
                        times for more output (e.g. -vvv).

commands:
  {monitor,instances,set-config}
                        See `zeek-client <command> -h` for per-command usage
                        info.
    monitor             For troubleshooting: do nothing, just report events.
    instances           Show instances connected to the controller.
    set-config          Deploy cluster configuration.
